# super-manus multi-author baseline (v0.9.7 R13).
#
# `merge=union` is git's built-in 3-way merge strategy for append-only ledgers:
# when two branches both append rows to the file, git keeps BOTH sets of new
# rows instead of reporting a same-line conflict at EOF.
#
# Applied ONLY to the two append-only project-state files. PRD (`prd/*.md`) and
# spec (`prd/*.spec.md`) are STRUCTURED documents, not ledgers — applying union
# to them would silently keep contradictory edits to the same `## Quality bar`
# bullet (Alice "200ms" + Bob "300ms" = both lines preserved, no conflict
# surfaced, PRD is now self-contradictory). git's default 3-way merge on PRD
# / spec correctly surfaces those as conflicts for a human to resolve.
#
# Do NOT add `prd/*.md`, `prd/*.spec.md`, or any structured document here.
# See docs/design-v0.9.7.md R13 for the full rationale.

docs/super-manus/drift_log.md merge=union
docs/super-manus/roadmap.md merge=union
